  "prompt": "When is India going to have plastic currency notes?",
  "response": "India has already introduced plastic currency notes in the form of polymer notes. The Reserve Bank of India (RBI) began testing these notes in 2016 with a limited issue of \u20b910 notes in a few locations. Polymer notes are more durable and can help reduce the cost of printing and replacement compared to traditional paper notes.\n\nAs of my last update in October 2023, there were ongoing discussions about the potential for more extensive use of polymer currency in India. However, the full-scale implementation and how quickly it will be adopted across all denominations would depend on various factors, including public response, logistics, and production capabilities.\n\nFor the most current information, it's advisable to check with official sources like the Reserve Bank of India or trusted news outlets.",
